If I remove the &quot;shareSideEffects()&quot; call, then each test will be 
excuted in its own test class instance, using Specsy&#39;s test isolation 
mechanism. But in this parameterized test it&#39;s much faster to disable 
the isolation, especially since the system under test is immutable so it 
doesn&#39;t need the isolation. This is how the results look without that 
optimization:

